title: Independent candidate Muhammad Idrees wins PK-86
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Muhammad Idrees won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-86, Nowshera-II by securing 38,030 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Awami National Party candidate Masood Abbas who bagged 12,860 votes.
Votersâ€™ turn-out remained at 47.63 per cent.
